Thank you for your anwser, so i don't have to add any DOT? I moved my TAO to Bitsensor wallet for this reason.

nope, you don't. Polkadot chain does have an "Existential Deposit" of 1 DOT, so any balance below that gets "reaped" (although the account still exists and can be revived as soon as it gets > 1 DOT), but that is of no consequence to a standalone substrate-based chain like Bittensor.

Basically, Bittensor really has nothing to do with Polkadot other than being built with Substrate, the blockchain framework created by the people who made Polkadot (and with which Polkadot is also built).
